>>CARLSON: All right.

00:48:09.930 --> 00:48:10.740 align:middle line:90%
Star tetrahedron.

00:48:10.740 --> 00:48:15.100 align:middle line:10%
Well, each tetrahedron is
measured by 720 degrees.

00:48:15.100 --> 00:48:18.890 align:middle line:10%
So the star tetrahedron was
measured by 1,440 degrees.

00:48:18.890 --> 00:48:22.190 align:middle line:10%
So there's a geometric
correlation to that.

00:48:22.190 --> 00:48:24.330 align:middle line:84%
In the Book of
Revelations, it's the wall

00:48:24.330 --> 00:48:26.800 align:middle line:84%
surrounding the Holy
City that's measured

00:48:26.800 --> 00:48:30.000 align:middle line:90%
by 144 cubits, these things.

00:48:30.000 --> 00:48:34.080 align:middle line:84%
Now, the standard Hebrew
cubit was a foot and a half.

00:48:34.080 --> 00:48:39.170 align:middle line:84%
So then if you convert
144 cubits to feet,

00:48:39.170 --> 00:48:44.740 align:middle line:84%
you get 216 feet,
or again, times 10

00:48:44.740 --> 00:48:46.430 align:middle line:90%
is the diameter of the moon.

00:48:46.430 --> 00:48:50.490 align:middle line:84%
So it's one of those key
numbers within this pattern,

00:48:50.490 --> 00:48:55.860 align:middle line:84%
within this hierarchy of
fractal self-similarity.

00:48:55.860 --> 00:48:58.680 align:middle line:84%
There's a story about
Joseph of Arimathea,

00:48:58.680 --> 00:49:01.845 align:middle line:84%
who removed the body of
Christ from the cross

00:49:01.845 --> 00:49:06.955 align:middle line:84%
and carried the holy grail
into Britain and founded

00:49:06.955 --> 00:49:07.455 align:middle line:90%
Glastonbury.

00:49:07.455 --> 00:49:08.420 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Glastonbury, yeah.

00:49:08.420 --> 00:49:08.790 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:49:08.790 --> 00:49:09.498 align:middle line:90%
>>CARLSON: Right.

00:49:09.498 --> 00:49:16.670 align:middle line:84%
And in the stories, he
created a small circular hut,

00:49:16.670 --> 00:49:19.510 align:middle line:84%
and then it was surrounded
by 12 huts around it,

00:49:19.510 --> 00:49:23.810 align:middle line:84%
where each of his 12
disciples would live.

00:49:23.810 --> 00:49:24.540 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:49:24.540 --> 00:49:27.220 align:middle line:84%
This is a model right there
of the Holy City, you see?

00:49:27.220 --> 00:49:33.230 align:middle line:84%
It's the model that we find
over and over again in Jesus

00:49:33.230 --> 00:49:37.280 align:middle line:84%
with 12 disciples,
Hercules with 12 labors,

00:49:37.280 --> 00:49:39.140 align:middle line:90%
Buddha with 12 disciples, right?

00:49:39.140 --> 00:49:40.330 align:middle line:90%
It goes on.

00:49:40.330 --> 00:49:43.840 align:middle line:84%
And geometrically, if
you have 12 spheres

00:49:43.840 --> 00:49:47.170 align:middle line:84%
of exactly the same size,
they will cluster perfectly

00:49:47.170 --> 00:49:48.865 align:middle line:90%
around a 13th.

00:49:48.865 --> 00:49:50.560 align:middle line:90%
You see?

00:49:50.560 --> 00:49:53.080 align:middle line:84%
So you have this
geometric clustering.

00:49:53.080 --> 00:49:56.970 align:middle line:84%
So in all of this stuff, there's
a geometric analog, you see.

00:49:56.970 --> 00:50:00.920 align:middle line:84%
And so I think what we're
ultimately talking about here

00:50:00.920 --> 00:50:06.270 align:middle line:84%
is we're looking behind
the outer forms of things

00:50:06.270 --> 00:50:10.200 align:middle line:84%
to see that there is a
pattern behind the outer form.

00:50:10.200 --> 00:50:12.770 align:middle line:84%
And we can recognize and
describe this pattern

00:50:12.770 --> 00:50:15.460 align:middle line:84%
by means of these
numbers, and these numbers

00:50:15.460 --> 00:50:18.234 align:middle line:84%
can describe patterns
both in space and in time.

00:50:18.234 --> 00:50:19.150 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And in time.

00:50:19.150 --> 00:50:19.774 align:middle line:90%
>>CARLSON: Yes.

