00:53:05.880 --> 00:53:07.940 align:middle line:84%
relates to each of
them in a certain way

00:53:07.940 --> 00:53:10.800 align:middle line:84%
and then can serve as a
unifying force between them.

00:53:10.800 --> 00:53:13.240 align:middle line:84%
That was a function
of the sacred temple.

00:53:13.240 --> 00:53:18.360 align:middle line:84%
It served as the geometrical
mean between the human scale

00:53:18.360 --> 00:53:20.310 align:middle line:90%
and the planetary scale.

00:53:20.310 --> 00:53:24.130 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And probably the
most significant of all those

00:53:24.130 --> 00:53:26.540 align:middle line:90%
would be the Great Pyramid.

00:53:26.540 --> 00:53:27.850 align:middle line:90%
>>CARLSON: Certainly yes.

00:53:27.850 --> 00:53:29.810 align:middle line:84%
In our day and age,
the most significant

00:53:29.810 --> 00:53:31.570 align:middle line:84%
is the Great Pyramid,
which embodies

00:53:31.570 --> 00:53:35.092 align:middle line:84%
this incredible geometry
based upon the golden section.

00:53:35.092 --> 00:53:36.550 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Same
thing, same numbers.

00:53:36.550 --> 00:53:39.350 align:middle line:84%
It all keeps coming back to
the same thing reflective

00:53:39.350 --> 00:53:41.560 align:middle line:90%
of Earth's dimensions herself.

00:53:41.560 --> 00:53:42.340 align:middle line:90%
>>CARLSON: Yes.

00:53:42.340 --> 00:53:44.860 align:middle line:84%
And if we scale
the Great Pyramid

00:53:44.860 --> 00:53:47.980 align:middle line:84%
up by a factor of
43,200, which is

00:53:47.980 --> 00:53:50.430 align:middle line:84%
one of the preeminent
sacred numbers.

00:53:50.430 --> 00:53:53.180 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, if
you think of this.

00:53:53.180 --> 00:53:56.340 align:middle line:84%
In a 24-hour day, Earth
turns on its axis.

00:53:56.340 --> 00:53:59.880 align:middle line:84%
Once that 24-hour
day is measured

00:53:59.880 --> 00:54:02.040 align:middle line:84%
between a point on the
surface of the Earth

00:54:02.040 --> 00:54:05.310 align:middle line:84%
and the position of the
sun-- so that if you picture

00:54:05.310 --> 00:54:08.680 align:middle line:84%
the sun as an orb with
a very precise dot

00:54:08.680 --> 00:54:13.400 align:middle line:84%
right in the center, just like
the astrological symbol, right?

00:54:13.400 --> 00:54:14.070 align:middle line:90%
OK

00:54:14.070 --> 00:54:16.300 align:middle line:90%
Now, Earth turns on its axis.

00:54:16.300 --> 00:54:19.380 align:middle line:84%
And each time a meridian
line exactly lines up

00:54:19.380 --> 00:54:22.720 align:middle line:84%
with the center of the sun,
that's one 24-hour day.

00:54:22.720 --> 00:54:23.540 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:54:23.540 --> 00:54:27.850 align:middle line:90%
24 hours times 60 is 1,440.

00:54:27.850 --> 00:54:31.920 align:middle line:84%
So there's 1,440
minutes in that cycle.

00:54:31.920 --> 00:54:37.380 align:middle line:84%
Then you multiply that times
60, and it's 86,400, right?

00:54:37.380 --> 00:54:39.360 align:middle line:84%
Add one zero on the
end of that, and it's

00:54:39.360 --> 00:54:44.600 align:middle line:84%
864,000, the measure of the
sun's diameter in miles, right?

00:54:44.600 --> 00:54:48.980 align:middle line:84%
It's also the measure
of one of the great ages

00:54:48.980 --> 00:54:52.390 align:middle line:84%
in Vedic system
called the Dwapara

00:54:52.390 --> 00:54:56.260 align:middle line:90%
Yuga, which was 864,000 years.

00:54:56.260 --> 00:54:58.880 align:middle line:84%
And the whole system of
the yugas was based--

00:54:58.880 --> 00:55:00.115 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Cycle of Brahma.

00:55:00.115 --> 00:55:00.740 align:middle line:90%
>>CARLSON: Yes.

00:55:00.740 --> 00:55:04.330 align:middle line:84%
But the yugas, the kalpas,
the whole cycle of Brahma

00:55:04.330 --> 00:55:10.480 align:middle line:84%
was based upon this
number 432, right, 432.

00:55:10.480 --> 00:55:15.300 align:middle line:84%
So we find that showing up in
frequencies in musical scales.

00:55:15.300 --> 00:55:17.220 align:middle line:84%
In, I think, the
Phrygian mode, I believe,

00:55:17.220 --> 00:55:21.990 align:middle line:90%
is where you find 432.

